00:45.160 --> 00:46.160
Listen up!

00:47.310 --> 00:49.590
This is your agent from now on.

00:49.590 --> 00:51.270
His name is Jin Du-ho.

00:51.740 --> 00:52.740
Hello!

00:55.160 --> 00:56.160
Huh?

00:56.630 --> 00:59.290
Korea Top Star regional preliminaries, Gangwon-do?

00:59.950 --> 01:01.030
Wild Ginseng Boys!

01:01.050 --> 01:02.240
Yeah, that's right.

01:02.240 --> 01:03.240
Thank you.

01:03.380 --> 01:05.790
- Hello.
- Hello.

01:05.870 --> 01:07.380
- Seriously.
- What? What? What?

01:07.380 --> 01:09.760
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Sir, come here. Come on.

01:10.340 --> 01:12.030
What's with his name?

01:12.070 --> 01:13.180
James or Edward.

01:13.180 --> 01:15.320
I said I wanted names like that!

01:15.350 --> 01:17.310
Whoa, were you serious?

01:17.310 --> 01:18.250
What the...

01:18.250 --> 01:19.920
Giving us a lame name

01:19.920 --> 01:22.030
might lead to our ruin.

01:22.030 --> 01:23.880
But you call us Cotton Candy?

01:23.880 --> 01:25.530
That's so embarrassing.

01:25.530 --> 01:28.000
Then go back to what it used to be.

01:28.120 --> 01:29.740
Seriously...

01:29.780 --> 01:30.770
Come on, sir!

01:30.770 --> 01:33.340
Hey, I love Cotton Candy.

01:33.520 --> 01:36.130
Since you'll be like cotton candy that gives

01:36.130 --> 01:39.850
comfort, happiness and love to the world.

01:40.170 --> 01:41.600
- Come on, Sir!
- What is he talking about?

01:41.630 --> 01:43.810
We'll be ruined because of our name.

01:43.810 --> 01:44.960
- Du-ho.
- Yes?

01:44.960 --> 01:46.130
Who are you a fan of in Cotton Candy?

01:46.130 --> 01:48.330
Oh, I'm a fan of...Oh Hyun-ji.

01:48.330 --> 01:50.200
Hyun-ji! He's your fan. Come here.

01:50.750 --> 01:51.750
Hyun-ji!

01:52.620 --> 01:54.530
No! Never!

01:55.220 --> 01:57.440
Since Du-ho is here, let's leave her out.

01:57.570 --> 01:58.759
Please do your best!

01:58.780 --> 01:59.539
Oh, yes.

01:59.570 --> 02:01.040
We look forward to working with you!

02:01.040 --> 02:02.320
I'll do my best.

02:02.600 --> 02:03.730
Fight on!

02:12.790 --> 02:16.660
Can you feel this trembling?

02:16.890 --> 02:21.470
Do you feel the same way?

02:21.520 --> 02:26.450
Time has stopped as if I'm in a dream

02:27.520 --> 02:30.230
Is this love?

02:32.210 --> 02:35.420
I look around and lovers are everywhere

02:35.680 --> 02:39.820
I was sad that I was alone

02:41.400 --> 02:44.970
But I saw you by my side

02:46.329 --> 02:47.810
What do you think this is?

02:50.020 --> 02:51.020
Dust?

02:51.829 --> 02:54.210
Wipe it all clean!

02:54.880 --> 02:55.880
Seriously!

02:58.140 --> 03:04.090
- Hello! We're Cotton Candy!
- Hello!

03:16.010 --> 03:18.780
- What?
- Leave! You're confusing me!

03:18.780 --> 03:20.650
Alright! I'll just watch!

03:25.800 --> 03:26.800
Eat up.

03:33.090 --> 03:34.530
What in the world?

03:34.690 --> 03:35.660
Oh! No, no, no.

03:35.660 --> 03:37.340
They're eating right now.

03:37.690 --> 03:39.690
You can get your photos later.

03:41.070 --> 03:42.930
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

03:43.020 --> 03:44.660
Huh? Where are you going?

03:46.900 --> 03:47.930
Hyun-ji!

03:52.520 --> 03:53.520
Come quick!

04:00.570 --> 04:02.500
- What?
- What are you doing?

04:04.280 --> 04:06.340
Imagining you and me walking together

04:06.340 --> 04:08.760
My cheeks blush as if I found happiness

04:08.760 --> 04:10.380
Even though the path we're walking on

04:10.380 --> 04:11.540
Is different for a while

04:11.540 --> 04:13.690
Let's hold hands tightly and walk together

04:13.690 --> 04:15.680
We're going to be a pretty couple

04:15.680 --> 04:18.880
I'll be your only lover

04:19.100 --> 04:21.870
Come closer to me

04:24.070 --> 04:25.050
Eat up, eat up.

04:25.050 --> 04:28.030
- Bon appetit!
- Bon appetit!

04:28.380 --> 04:30.910
No, it's okay. You guys eat. I'm fine.

04:30.950 --> 04:34.030
We don't give drumsticks to just anyone. Eat up.

04:34.440 --> 04:35.800
Come on, take it.

04:35.840 --> 04:36.840
Take it.

04:37.150 --> 04:38.320
Thank you.

04:49.920 --> 04:50.920
Awesome!

04:51.159 --> 04:51.970
Du-ho.

04:52.170 --> 04:55.050
Was your dream to become a singer?

04:55.460 --> 04:56.460
No.

04:57.060 --> 04:58.350
Then why did you

04:59.030 --> 05:01.030
go on a dancing competition show?

05:02.580 --> 05:04.690
I danced at the village party.

05:05.290 --> 05:07.630
Everyone said I was good and suggested it.

05:08.530 --> 05:10.930
That's why you failed.

05:11.570 --> 05:14.200
You have to have a dream.

05:16.370 --> 05:19.000
When CEO Ma introduced me to you,

05:19.650 --> 05:21.330
I felt like my ancestors

05:21.820 --> 05:24.340
gave me a second chance in life.

05:24.750 --> 05:26.360
I believed so.

05:27.620 --> 05:29.000
To be a good agent

05:29.180 --> 05:30.900
for the successful Cotton Candy.

05:35.000 --> 05:36.560
That's my dream.

05:37.010 --> 05:38.110
So you all

05:38.540 --> 05:39.820
have to make it.

05:45.070 --> 05:46.070
My girls...

05:48.350 --> 05:49.850
What will happen to them?

06:14.400 --> 06:15.530
Seobit Medical Center Funeral Hall

06:21.500 --> 06:23.060
They're here.

09:09.830 --> 09:15.270
Part 4
How to Use Your 1% Potential

09:21.420 --> 09:22.490
Interview with New CEO Cha Jae-hyuk

09:22.250 --> 09:24.960
Your priority is going public, right?

09:24.990 --> 09:25.990
Of course.

09:26.300 --> 09:28.150
That's the biggest reason

09:28.150 --> 09:29.880
the board hired me.

09:32.570 --> 09:33.760
In order to go public,

09:34.270 --> 09:35.870
I will, by and large,

09:37.090 --> 09:38.770
clean up the company.

09:39.300 --> 09:41.740
- Please write a good article for us.
- Don't worry.

09:41.740 --> 09:43.720
- Goodbye. Goodbye.
- Bye.

09:45.810 --> 09:46.810
Hey.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.520
It's Cotton Candy's file.

09:48.520 --> 09:50.060
Tomorrow's the meeting.

09:50.760 --> 09:52.040
CEO Ma

09:52.180 --> 09:53.520
was going to give Cotton Candy

09:53.520 --> 09:55.470
another chance. Director Yoon told me.

09:55.470 --> 09:56.470
Really?

09:57.310 --> 09:58.750
But it's all over.

10:00.170 --> 10:01.650
It doesn't look too good.

10:01.930 --> 10:03.080
People think the reason Du-ho died

10:03.080 --> 10:04.650
was because of Cotton Candy.

10:06.590 --> 10:08.300
I heard the CEO died as well.

10:08.300 --> 10:10.330
What if the unit group of Mars gets pushed back?

10:10.330 --> 10:12.490
This is all that failed idol group's fault.

10:12.490 --> 10:13.610
Crazy jerks.

10:13.960 --> 10:15.650
A person has died.

10:17.010 --> 10:18.750
You call yourselves human?

10:19.040 --> 10:20.320
A person has died.

10:20.320 --> 10:22.120
You trash idiots!

10:22.220 --> 10:23.590
Stop it!

10:25.100 --> 10:26.250
Crazy fools.

10:26.940 --> 10:28.740
I'm going to kill them all!

10:33.000 --> 10:34.680
Do something about her.

10:34.720 --> 10:36.400
She's driving me crazy.

10:45.210 --> 10:47.130
Stop it, please!

10:47.130 --> 10:48.660
What do they know?

10:48.660 --> 10:49.980
How dare they!

10:50.420 --> 10:52.980
This won't help. It's useless!

10:52.980 --> 10:54.370
Let go!

10:55.730 --> 10:57.860
I'm going to rip them to pieces!

11:09.750 --> 11:10.750
Jenna.

11:13.210 --> 11:15.390
I think Hyun-ji will get in big trouble.

11:15.640 --> 11:16.480
She won't sleep.

11:16.480 --> 11:17.960
She chases after fan websites

11:17.960 --> 11:19.060
and fights with people.

11:20.430 --> 11:21.620
Go stop her.

11:23.070 --> 11:24.590
She listens to you.

11:25.310 --> 11:26.310
Huh?

11:32.250 --> 11:33.250
Jenna.

11:34.770 --> 11:36.450
You can't be like this.

11:40.470 --> 11:42.490
Then tell me what to do.

11:44.100 --> 11:45.780
Since you're like this,

11:45.850 --> 11:47.680
it seems like it's really all over.

11:49.600 --> 11:50.720
Du-ho wouldn't

11:52.530 --> 11:54.190
have wanted this.

12:01.230 --> 12:04.030
How do you know what a dead person thinks?

12:07.360 --> 12:08.360
Stella.

12:10.620 --> 12:12.060
Don't do anything.

12:15.830 --> 12:17.030
We're finished.

12:21.250 --> 12:23.160
Stella! Stella!

12:23.570 --> 12:25.250
It's Hyun-ji!

12:31.450 --> 12:33.980
Is it true that Highteen's agent bravely died

12:33.980 --> 12:35.650
while trying to promote a failed idol group?

12:35.650 --> 12:37.340
He should've died trying to promote Highteen.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.080
Why'd he sacrifice himself for a failed group?

12:39.100 --> 12:40.880
You're not even human.

12:41.050 --> 12:42.760
Die and go to hell!

12:42.890 --> 12:44.660
Your parents and siblings as well!

12:44.660 --> 12:47.240
Are you Cotton Candy? Why flip out?

12:47.240 --> 12:49.440
Yeah, I'm Cotton Candy's Hyun-ji.

12:49.460 --> 12:51.580
If you're so great, reveal yourselves! Don't hide.

12:51.580 --> 12:54.650
Seriously? She's here in person. Awesome.

12:54.700 --> 12:56.640
I'm better than you, failed idol singer.

12:56.640 --> 12:58.160
Come out! Come out!

12:58.360 --> 13:00.680
Let's see if you can do this in person!

13:00.680 --> 13:02.910
Whoa, real life player kill? State the place.

13:02.910 --> 13:04.040
Let's see a failed idol's face.

13:04.040 --> 13:05.330
Don't hightail it and write the address.

13:05.330 --> 13:06.340
I'm coming now.

13:06.340 --> 13:07.630
You think we'll be intimidated?

13:07.630 --> 13:09.530
Come to Center Internet CafÃ© in Sangam-dong.

13:09.530 --> 13:10.610
We'll wait until 10 PM.

13:10.610 --> 13:12.030
You're so dead!

13:23.410 --> 13:24.180
You thought

13:24.200 --> 13:26.200
we'd be scared because you're a celebrity?

13:27.320 --> 13:28.950
You can't do a thing, but you acted so fierce?

13:29.490 --> 13:31.290
You're full of spirit, huh?

13:31.580 --> 13:34.160
You should've sung with this spirit.

13:34.190 --> 13:36.620
Then you wouldn't have failed.

13:36.950 --> 13:39.400
It's true the dead guy isn't your agent, right?

13:39.720 --> 13:40.670
Because of him,

13:40.670 --> 13:42.730
you nobodies got famous, right?

13:42.750 --> 13:44.210
Then he did die after promoting

13:44.210 --> 13:45.650
you nobodies, right?

13:45.650 --> 13:46.860
Am I wrong?

13:47.190 --> 13:49.720
Why flip out and call us out at night?

13:51.360 --> 13:52.360
Hey!

13:52.660 --> 13:55.240
Let go! Let go!

14:08.620 --> 14:11.730
Why does what Du-ho does always fall apart?

14:11.950 --> 14:14.500
You're half the reason we failed!

14:14.500 --> 14:15.360
I'll be there soon.

14:15.360 --> 14:16.980
Go to a nearby coffee shop.

14:17.110 --> 14:19.470
There's no coffee shop in this countryside!

14:20.950 --> 14:23.040
That's enough. Let's go.

15:03.500 --> 15:04.890
Chae-ah! She's not there?

15:04.890 --> 15:05.890
No.

15:05.990 --> 15:07.640
- Where is she?
- Let's try over there.

15:07.920 --> 15:09.840
- Hyun-ji!
- Hyun-ji!

15:10.580 --> 15:11.580
Hyun-ji!

15:12.210 --> 15:13.210
Hyun-ji!

15:13.540 --> 15:14.750
Oh Hyun-ji!

15:16.630 --> 15:17.290
Hey!

15:17.290 --> 15:18.160
Are you okay?

15:18.210 --> 15:20.280
So why did you do that?

15:20.280 --> 15:21.280
Hyun-ji!

15:38.470 --> 15:39.570
Cotton Candy Expenditures Itemized

15:39.610 --> 15:41.420
It costs more to maintain this group

15:41.420 --> 15:43.100
than to breach their contract.

15:43.100 --> 15:45.300
Talk of early disbanding came up continuously.

15:46.080 --> 15:48.850
Well, CEO Ma couldn't make a decision.

15:49.020 --> 15:49.900
Why?

15:49.940 --> 15:51.200
They're the founding members.

15:51.200 --> 15:53.050
He has a lot of affection for them.

15:55.110 --> 15:56.710
I guess that's important

15:56.780 --> 15:57.970
to this company.

15:59.360 --> 16:01.090
Are there no other reasons

16:01.130 --> 16:02.730
for keeping them on?

16:04.810 --> 16:06.610
What do you all think?

16:07.690 --> 16:08.900
This group...

16:10.080 --> 16:11.080
Is there

16:12.490 --> 16:13.490
potential?

16:27.390 --> 16:29.680
Bbiyong wrote a new song for our unit.

16:29.980 --> 16:31.340
Check your email.

16:32.070 --> 16:33.750
He has a new concept.

16:33.890 --> 16:34.890
By the way,

16:35.300 --> 16:37.570
didn't you rearrange the previous song?

16:38.750 --> 16:40.920
I just did it because I was frustrated.

16:42.320 --> 16:44.060
Go to the office tomorrow.

16:44.280 --> 16:45.720
It's been 2 weeks.

16:45.890 --> 16:46.930
Go say hello.

16:48.300 --> 16:49.980
Whenever I played this,

16:52.080 --> 16:53.760
CEO Ma snorted, you know?

17:02.410 --> 17:04.609
I changed the lyrics to diss him.

17:06.750 --> 17:08.160
Half of it was cursing him.

17:13.720 --> 17:14.720
One time,

17:15.880 --> 17:16.550
in the studio,

17:16.550 --> 17:18.349
I was singing my heart out.

17:20.099 --> 17:21.270
CEO Ma

17:21.920 --> 17:24.490
You must not know who to thank

17:24.560 --> 17:26.220
I guess you'd think you succeeded

17:26.220 --> 17:28.190
But everyone knows (yeah)

17:28.290 --> 17:31.570
You're a pot-bellied old man with a 40-inch waist

17:31.910 --> 17:32.590
Look in the mirror

17:32.610 --> 17:35.420
You lack sense like you lack hair

17:35.540 --> 17:38.850
Come on, old man, don't act that way

17:39.200 --> 17:41.930
Your rambling speech hurts my ears

17:41.930 --> 17:45.990
You'd kill for my abs, no doubt

17:49.650 --> 17:51.760
I didn't know it, but he was listening.

17:51.920 --> 17:53.200
I was so scared.

17:53.990 --> 17:56.900
But he changed the words and dissed me right back.

18:00.200 --> 18:02.250
The lyrics were so childish.

18:03.890 --> 18:05.570
But they were sincere.

18:09.650 --> 18:11.100
It really stuck with me.

18:11.130 --> 18:13.190
Have you ever done a rap battle with an old man?

18:13.480 --> 18:14.310
Ji-han.

18:14.310 --> 18:16.040
I knelt right away like a man.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.950
He sometimes won me over like that.

18:24.130 --> 18:25.220
If you're not seeing CEO Cha

18:25.220 --> 18:26.450
because you can't let CEO Ma go...

18:27.510 --> 18:28.460
You're wrong.

18:33.030 --> 18:34.860
I haven't let CEO Ma go yet.

18:37.280 --> 18:39.300
But that's not why I can't accept that jerk.

18:40.820 --> 18:42.390
I just don't want to see him.

18:43.550 --> 18:44.550
That jerk

18:46.490 --> 18:47.530
is perverted.

18:47.740 --> 18:49.630
Even a tiny bit of potential.

18:49.630 --> 18:53.300
When you say "tiny," how much do you mean?

18:54.750 --> 18:57.630
1% potential is the best.

18:59.700 --> 19:01.250
With absurd logic...

19:01.250 --> 19:02.250
1%?

19:03.920 --> 19:06.490
He stabs a dagger in your heart and enjoys it!

19:06.490 --> 19:08.480
If there's even 1% potential,

19:08.920 --> 19:10.650
then I give them a chance.

19:10.920 --> 19:12.350
I get out my calculator later.

19:12.350 --> 19:14.210
He's an arrogant narcissist.

19:18.870 --> 19:21.250
The reason 1% potential is the best

19:22.990 --> 19:25.400
is because no one will bet on it.

19:25.710 --> 19:26.910
Because it means

19:27.190 --> 19:29.190
you take the biggest bite.

19:30.480 --> 19:31.860
But still,

19:31.860 --> 19:34.180
betting on 1% is too big of a risk.

19:34.490 --> 19:35.990
Reducing the risk

19:36.090 --> 19:37.770
is your job, isn't?

19:39.420 --> 19:41.270
So tell me.

19:43.440 --> 19:44.640
Does this group

19:45.770 --> 19:47.410
have that 1% potential

19:47.820 --> 19:48.970
to make it?

19:49.310 --> 19:50.310
In one word,

19:51.110 --> 19:52.630
he's not trustworthy.

19:55.010 --> 19:56.010
1%?

19:56.370 --> 19:58.630
Why do we have to reduce the risk?

19:59.330 --> 20:01.010
To put the blame on us?

20:01.630 --> 20:03.540
They say he's the Midas touch in investment.

20:03.540 --> 20:04.910
There was a reason for it.

20:04.910 --> 20:06.980
Midas, my foot. Minus is more like it.

20:07.690 --> 20:09.520
He's a calculator handling money.

20:09.550 --> 20:11.290
What does he know?

20:11.910 --> 20:14.440
The ability to recognize a talent in this business

20:15.130 --> 20:16.830
is a composite art.

20:17.320 --> 20:19.250
Didn't you know?

20:19.380 --> 20:20.390
CEO Cha,

20:20.390 --> 20:22.150
before he joined an investment company,

20:22.150 --> 20:23.160
he was a competent A&R

20:23.160 --> 20:24.770
in an American agency.

20:24.110 --> 20:26.320
A&R: Responsible for talent scouting,
overseeing the artist's artistic development,

20:24.890 --> 20:26.190
- Really?
- Yes!

20:26.320 --> 20:28.260
discovering songs that fit,
drawing a contract and production

20:26.600 --> 20:28.300
So what? Huh?

20:29.100 --> 20:30.100
Sir.

20:31.210 --> 20:33.710
Is it true CEO Ma was going to give Cotton Candy

20:33.920 --> 20:34.960
another chance?

20:36.630 --> 20:37.220
Yes.

20:37.220 --> 20:38.280
Shouldn't we tell them?

20:38.280 --> 20:39.100
Who?

20:39.450 --> 20:40.540
The girls?

20:41.040 --> 20:42.980
You want to kill them twice?

20:49.100 --> 20:50.130
I also think

20:51.060 --> 20:52.660
that team has no potential.

20:52.660 --> 20:54.630
Then why did you ask us earlier?

20:55.130 --> 20:57.030
Because I want to know what you think.

20:57.210 --> 20:58.390
Weren't all of you

20:58.920 --> 21:00.150
negative about it?

21:01.560 --> 21:02.700
Give them one more chance.

21:02.700 --> 21:03.250
Hey.

21:03.270 --> 21:04.560
What chance?

21:04.630 --> 21:05.630
Sir.

21:06.260 --> 21:08.650
Think of it as CEO Ma's dying wishes.

21:09.330 --> 21:11.760
You mean you want them to know

21:13.240 --> 21:15.950
that they don't have even 1% potential?

21:17.800 --> 21:19.480
Isn't that too cruel?

21:23.950 --> 21:26.140
She let them beat her up.

21:29.620 --> 21:31.250
She thinks Du-ho's accident

21:31.680 --> 21:33.560
was because of her.

21:37.760 --> 21:38.760
Jenna.

21:38.970 --> 21:40.650
Please say something.

21:44.420 --> 21:46.960
Whatever she thinks, it's on her.

21:48.580 --> 21:49.860
Her thoughts are her own.

22:13.100 --> 22:14.400
To be a good agent

22:14.400 --> 22:16.190
for the successful Cotton Candy.

22:17.690 --> 22:19.980
So you all have to make it.

22:24.100 --> 22:25.360
I lost.

22:30.200 --> 22:32.120
I lost!

