Don't wanna feel it if it's without ya

58:01.950 --> 58:03.210
If I'm honest

58:05.960 --> 58:07.470
If I'm honest

58:23.230 --> 58:25.030
They did such a good job!

59:04.160 --> 59:05.120
Yeah.

59:41.910 --> 59:42.910
You did well.

59:43.540 --> 59:46.450
It was worth the practice.

59:46.650 --> 59:48.450
Thank you!

59:50.720 --> 59:52.000
Well, then.

59:53.340 --> 59:54.510
Did you all have fun?

59:54.510 --> 59:55.890
Yes!

59:57.860 --> 59:58.860
Good.

59:59.630 --> 1:00:00.860
Okay, then.

1:00:01.530 --> 1:00:02.830
How much

1:00:04.400 --> 1:00:06.930
do you think this group will earn us?

1:00:17.740 --> 1:00:18.860
Director Yoon!

1:00:20.110 --> 1:00:21.180
Speak.

1:00:21.510 --> 1:00:23.220
How much do you think Cotton Candy

1:00:23.220 --> 1:00:24.900
will earn for Starpeace?

1:00:26.250 --> 1:00:29.190
This is sudden. I don't know what to say.

1:00:30.690 --> 1:00:34.060
If we newly package Cotton Candy,

1:00:34.060 --> 1:00:36.140
those who think we'll pass the break-even point

1:00:36.140 --> 1:00:37.160
within a year,

1:00:37.630 --> 1:00:38.900
raise your hand.

1:00:54.280 --> 1:00:57.480
If even one person can responsibly guarantee that,

1:00:57.920 --> 1:01:01.290
this group will remain as Starpeace's artist.

1:01:10.830 --> 1:01:11.830
No one?

1:01:14.770 --> 1:01:15.970
Not even one?

1:01:22.970 --> 1:01:23.970
Me!

1:01:32.280 --> 1:01:33.400
Director Yoon!

1:01:33.520 --> 1:01:34.390
Yes?

1:01:34.390 --> 1:01:38.460
Is Seo Ji-han a staff member of Starpeace?

1:01:39.120 --> 1:01:40.260
No.

1:01:43.430 --> 1:01:45.760
You promised!

1:01:47.270 --> 1:01:49.170
To be fair!

1:01:58.610 --> 1:02:00.310
We did really well.

1:02:01.450 --> 1:02:03.320
You saw the response.

1:02:03.320 --> 1:02:04.520
You did do well.

1:02:04.520 --> 1:02:05.080
Then?

1:02:05.080 --> 1:02:07.190
Whether you're a good product is different.

1:02:08.090 --> 1:02:09.990
Everyone is saying that.

1:02:12.260 --> 1:02:15.990
You were unable to persuade

1:02:15.990 --> 1:02:17.830
even one person here.

1:02:28.470 --> 1:02:30.410
I can't accept this.

1:02:32.410 --> 1:02:34.380
Look me in the eye

1:02:34.750 --> 1:02:36.750
and tell me we're not competent.

1:02:36.750 --> 1:02:37.850
Say it.

1:02:38.950 --> 1:02:40.490
You are competent.

1:02:43.420 --> 1:02:44.760
You're just not appealing.

1:02:50.100 --> 1:02:52.330
Practicing night and day to get the perfect moves

1:02:52.330 --> 1:02:54.430
and singing with excellent vocal skills

1:02:55.100 --> 1:02:56.770
don't make you an appealing team.

1:02:56.770 --> 1:02:57.770
Furthermore,

1:02:58.040 --> 1:03:01.440
the stage, hair, makeup and costume were the best.

1:03:02.570 --> 1:03:03.910
But you couldn't provide more than

1:03:03.910 --> 1:03:05.380
momentary entertainment.

1:03:05.380 --> 1:03:06.810
That's enough!

1:03:21.230 --> 1:03:24.230
It means you don't even have a 1% potential.

1:03:30.970 --> 1:03:32.360
You crook!

1:03:32.360 --> 1:03:33.120
Hyun-ji...

1:03:33.150 --> 1:03:35.840
This is why I told you to give up.

1:03:35.840 --> 1:03:38.010
You wanted to end up like this?

1:03:38.280 --> 1:03:41.410
The remaining contract period is meaningless.

1:03:41.410 --> 1:03:43.620
I want this sorted as soon as possible.

1:03:43.620 --> 1:03:45.880
I'll compensate according to your contract.

1:03:46.150 --> 1:03:47.590
Okay.

1:03:50.160 --> 1:03:51.260
Jenna.

1:03:54.560 --> 1:03:55.730
You're firing us.

1:03:56.460 --> 1:03:58.030
I'll accept that.

1:03:59.400 --> 1:04:01.070
But let us

1:04:01.530 --> 1:04:03.870
leave with our name, Cotton Candy.

1:04:10.440 --> 1:04:11.640
Director Yoon!

1:04:12.510 --> 1:04:12.910
Yes?

1:04:12.910 --> 1:04:14.270
Is that possible?

1:04:14.510 --> 1:04:15.850
Is there precedent?

1:04:16.180 --> 1:04:17.750
The team name is a trademark right.

1:04:17.750 --> 1:04:18.650
An asset of the company.

1:04:18.650 --> 1:04:23.050
But Starpeace doesn't need Cotton Candy.

1:04:23.150 --> 1:04:24.420
We can't become a precedent.

1:04:24.420 --> 1:04:25.420
Director Yoon!

1:04:25.420 --> 1:04:27.130
Don't say such idiotic crap!

1:04:27.130 --> 1:04:28.190
Hyun-ji! Come on.

1:04:28.190 --> 1:04:29.730
Stop speak so roughly.

1:04:29.730 --> 1:04:31.460
You guys started it!

1:04:31.460 --> 1:04:32.430
Hyun-ji! Come on.

1:04:32.430 --> 1:04:34.330
Take her away.

1:04:37.240 --> 1:04:38.240
You heard, right?

1:04:38.500 --> 1:04:39.670
No.

1:04:40.810 --> 1:04:42.910
Then give us 3 months.

1:04:43.980 --> 1:04:46.780
Jenna! What will you do in 3 months?

1:04:47.310 --> 1:04:48.850
We won't be fired.

1:04:50.820 --> 1:04:52.220
We'll disband.

1:04:56.590 --> 1:04:59.820
But where and how

1:04:59.820 --> 1:05:02.030
will be decided by us.

1:05:05.400 --> 1:05:07.700
Are you going to hold a press conference?

1:05:08.370 --> 1:05:10.400
We'll be No.1 in a music TV show,

1:05:10.400 --> 1:05:12.840
then announce that we're disbanding.

1:05:23.750 --> 1:05:25.150
What's up with her?

1:05:25.150 --> 1:05:26.690
She must be crazy.

1:05:26.950 --> 1:05:28.320
Kim Jenna...

1:05:29.420 --> 1:05:31.020
What are you thinking?

1:05:33.990 --> 1:05:35.830
Why is she doing this?

1:05:38.200 --> 1:05:39.880
I think you're in shock.

1:05:40.570 --> 1:05:42.130
Go get some rest.

1:05:43.070 --> 1:05:45.300
Then we'll take our name and leave!

1:05:49.840 --> 1:05:50.740
No!

1:05:50.740 --> 1:05:52.280
Then give us 3 months.

1:05:52.280 --> 1:05:53.210
No!

1:05:53.210 --> 1:05:55.180
Why do you keep saying no?

1:05:55.180 --> 1:05:56.180
Since you're speaking nonsense!

1:05:56.180 --> 1:05:58.080
Why is it nonsense?

1:05:58.080 --> 1:05:59.780
Remove your foot first!

1:06:07.160 --> 1:06:09.260
Why can't you give us

1:06:09.260 --> 1:06:11.260
that short time?

1:06:11.260 --> 1:06:12.730
Why, why, why!

1:06:13.230 --> 1:06:15.330
Stop asking why. Okay?

1:06:17.170 --> 1:06:18.900
About the breach of contract...

1:06:18.900 --> 1:06:20.740
I'll fight you with everything I have.

1:06:21.140 --> 1:06:22.810
You have no chance of winning!

1:06:22.810 --> 1:06:23.980
I don't care.

1:06:23.980 --> 1:06:25.240
I've been labeled as a failed idol singer.

1:06:25.240 --> 1:06:26.680
A few years is nothing.

1:06:26.680 --> 1:06:28.710
You say time is money. I'll drag you down

1:06:28.710 --> 1:06:31.080
and take you on a long dirty fight in court.

1:06:31.080 --> 1:06:32.750
I have all the time in the world.

1:06:32.750 --> 1:06:34.090
And you'll find out soon enough,

1:06:34.490 --> 1:06:35.990
but I am very

1:06:35.990 --> 1:06:37.620
persistent.

1:06:41.360 --> 1:06:43.560
Our Jenna is a fighter.

1:06:45.800 --> 1:06:46.500
What are you doing?

1:06:46.500 --> 1:06:47.630
Villain.

1:06:48.870 --> 1:06:50.500
Can she do that?

1:07:00.550 --> 1:07:01.610
Okay.

1:07:02.180 --> 1:07:04.880
Prove that you're worth receiving 3 months' time.

1:07:05.180 --> 1:07:05.980
How?

1:07:05.980 --> 1:07:07.290
In 3 days,

1:07:07.950 --> 1:07:09.750
become so famous that people forget

1:07:09.750 --> 1:07:11.260
you were labeled a failed idol singer.

1:07:14.930 --> 1:07:16.060
I told you.

1:07:16.830 --> 1:07:18.060
He's perverted.

1:07:20.570 --> 1:07:21.700
What's the criteria?

1:07:22.070 --> 1:07:23.330
Director Yoon!

1:07:23.840 --> 1:07:24.740
Yes?

1:07:25.200 --> 1:07:27.570
There's a famous entertainment journalist, right?

1:07:27.570 --> 1:07:29.250
Entertainment journalist?

1:07:31.180 --> 1:07:32.180
Mo Ga...?

1:07:33.080 --> 1:07:34.450
Oh, Reporter Mo Ga-jin...

1:07:34.450 --> 1:07:36.350
He's a slight wacko.

1:07:36.350 --> 1:07:38.520
Make him stalk you!

1:07:41.250 --> 1:07:42.290
Sir.

1:07:42.820 --> 1:07:44.820
He won't even see you if you're not a top star.

1:07:44.820 --> 1:07:46.020
Precisely.

1:07:52.330 --> 1:07:53.600
It's 3 days.

1:07:55.070 --> 1:07:57.040
If you can't do it in 3 days,

1:07:57.900 --> 1:07:59.440
you'll leave, stripped of everything.

1:08:00.740 --> 1:08:01.740
Okay?

1:08:02.240 --> 1:08:03.270
Okay!

1:08:22.040 --> 1:08:23.430
What's with her?

1:08:23.430 --> 1:08:25.359
Jenna, why are you doing this?

1:08:25.359 --> 1:08:26.430
Yeah, Jenna.

1:08:26.430 --> 1:08:28.700
Why are you doing this? Huh? Why?

1:08:28.970 --> 1:08:31.540
Director Yoon, you traitor!

1:08:32.200 --> 1:08:32.939
Hyun-ji.

1:08:32.939 --> 1:08:36.069
I was never on your side.

1:08:36.270 --> 1:08:37.630
How could you side with

1:08:37.630 --> 1:08:39.850
a stone that just rolled in?

1:08:39.880 --> 1:08:42.580
We were here before you!

1:08:42.580 --> 1:08:45.620
We made this agency, you filthy traitor!

1:08:48.020 --> 1:08:49.290
I'm old enough to be your uncle.

1:08:49.290 --> 1:08:52.189
Don't be so rude in front of others!

1:08:52.260 --> 1:08:55.060
Uncle? Uncle, my foot!

1:08:55.060 --> 1:08:56.560
I'm an orphan!

1:09:02.800 --> 1:09:04.270
- Hold me.
- Okay.

1:09:04.870 --> 1:09:05.870
Let's go.

1:09:43.740 --> 1:09:45.439
What's this? A change of players?

1:09:45.439 --> 1:09:46.479
I have something to say.

1:09:46.479 --> 1:09:47.880
I have nothing to hear!

1:09:47.880 --> 1:09:50.010
CEO Ma said when he disbands us,

1:09:50.279 --> 1:09:52.580
he'll leave me on as a solo artist.

1:09:53.520 --> 1:09:56.350
He said that because I'm worth it as a solo act.

1:09:57.190 --> 1:09:58.620
I hope you can

1:10:00.120 --> 1:10:01.960
consider that.

1:10:05.000 --> 1:10:07.030
I can see for sure why your team

1:10:07.230 --> 1:10:08.930
didn't work out.

1:10:14.740 --> 1:10:15.740
Elle.

1:10:19.080 --> 1:10:23.920
I like selfish and ambitious characters like you.

1:10:24.150 --> 1:10:25.020
Why?

1:10:25.020 --> 1:10:26.140
Because you're straightforward

1:10:26.140 --> 1:10:28.200
and you sort the situation simply.

1:10:28.690 --> 1:10:31.350
But that's different from product value.

1:10:32.190 --> 1:10:34.060
I said it earlier.

1:10:34.760 --> 1:10:37.360
There are tons of excellent singers like you.

1:10:37.600 --> 1:10:38.600
And

1:10:39.330 --> 1:10:41.530
your character overlaps with Lune.

1:10:41.530 --> 1:10:43.700
CEO Ma must've known that.

1:10:48.940 --> 1:10:51.740
Hey. Why are you here?

1:10:54.950 --> 1:10:56.350
Seriously.

1:10:56.950 --> 1:10:58.680
I'm going mad.

1:11:00.520 --> 1:11:01.520
Sir!

1:11:01.820 --> 1:11:03.150
Why make things get out of hand?

1:11:03.150 --> 1:11:04.960
Just disband them!

1:11:04.960 --> 1:11:06.760
Don't you feel sorry for them?

1:11:16.000 --> 1:11:17.470
They challenged my judgment

1:11:18.340 --> 1:11:20.200
and my authority.

1:11:20.940 --> 1:11:21.940
What?

1:11:25.840 --> 1:11:26.880
He's a wacko.

1:11:27.680 --> 1:11:29.710
He must be a psychopath.

1:11:29.710 --> 1:11:32.220
He might roam around at night with a knife.

1:11:36.550 --> 1:11:38.230
Did Elle leave already?

1:11:43.530 --> 1:11:45.700
At least, the rooster is loyal.

1:11:45.860 --> 1:11:47.370
Should I be moved?

1:11:49.900 --> 1:11:51.340
Don't trust CEO Cha.

1:11:51.700 --> 1:11:52.840
If I don't?

1:11:53.340 --> 1:11:55.410
Should I say I won't take this test?

1:11:55.610 --> 1:11:56.670
Now?

1:11:57.780 --> 1:11:59.680
I don't trust CEO Cha.

1:12:01.010 --> 1:12:02.450
I trust us.

1:12:06.450 --> 1:12:07.500
By the way...

1:12:09.690 --> 1:12:12.390
Why do you hate him so much?

1:12:17.760 --> 1:12:19.660
He did this to me once.

1:12:22.430 --> 1:12:25.170
That all I had to do was show him 1% potential.

1:12:26.870 --> 1:12:28.940
I don't know if this will help.

1:12:29.870 --> 1:12:33.280
But he can't stand to lose in small things.

1:12:35.410 --> 1:12:36.780
That's your chance.

1:12:40.750 --> 1:12:41.850
Jenna!

1:12:42.320 --> 1:12:43.990
Good job!

1:12:44.260 --> 1:12:45.760
Even if it was rambling nonsense,

1:12:45.760 --> 1:12:47.860
I felt like a huge weight was lifted!

1:12:47.860 --> 1:12:48.760
Right!

1:12:48.960 --> 1:12:50.960
It's not rambling nonsense?

1:12:51.460 --> 1:12:52.330
Nope.

1:12:52.330 --> 1:12:54.270
You're really planning to go on a music show

1:12:54.270 --> 1:12:55.800
and become No.1?

1:12:55.930 --> 1:12:56.830
Yep.

1:12:57.340 --> 1:12:58.700
Then we'll really

1:13:01.110 --> 1:13:02.670
disband?

1:13:11.280 --> 1:13:13.720
The world mocked us, saying we were finished.

1:13:16.620 --> 1:13:18.390
I pretended not to hear.

1:13:21.060 --> 1:13:23.360
And I asked for one more chance.

1:13:24.630 --> 1:13:26.930
I said we could do really well.

1:13:28.170 --> 1:13:29.530
I begged.

1:13:30.540 --> 1:13:31.940
I groveled.

1:13:37.210 --> 1:13:38.640
But...

1:13:41.250 --> 1:13:42.370
I didn't know.

1:13:43.080 --> 1:13:45.180
The reason I went to such lengths...

1:13:47.450 --> 1:13:49.890
There must've been a reason.

1:13:51.990 --> 1:13:54.090
But I couldn't think of it no matter what.

1:13:57.760 --> 1:13:58.760
But

1:13:59.830 --> 1:14:03.800
now I know why.

1:14:06.040 --> 1:14:10.110
This... Is it.

1:14:11.840 --> 1:14:13.540
We have to stop here.

1:14:24.920 --> 1:14:27.930
But we can't go out like this.

1:14:29.090 --> 1:14:30.660
We worked so hard!

1:14:32.100 --> 1:14:34.230
We should have at least one memory of success.

1:14:35.200 --> 1:14:36.970
It'd be good to end like that.

1:14:39.700 --> 1:14:41.440
Then I won't regret anything.

1:14:43.340 --> 1:14:45.310
I don't want to regret who I am from now on.

1:14:46.040 --> 1:14:47.680
What I was looking for

1:14:47.910 --> 1:14:49.580
wasn't one chance,

1:14:50.650 --> 1:14:52.320
but one success.

1:15:00.420 --> 1:15:01.990
We're going to stop?

1:15:02.360 --> 1:15:06.040
We're really quitting?

1:15:13.840 --> 1:15:15.640
I'm sorry I made the decision alone.

1:15:16.770 --> 1:15:18.810
If you're against it, tell me now.

1:15:20.910 --> 1:15:22.110
I agree!

1:15:23.450 --> 1:15:24.750
I agree!

1:15:27.850 --> 1:15:31.990
I'm going to break out of this booth!

1:15:33.320 --> 1:15:35.290
I'm going to become an adult in the outside world!

1:15:43.670 --> 1:15:44.970
Darn it...

1:15:46.500 --> 1:15:48.910
This is crappy...

1:15:50.780 --> 1:15:55.250
But okay! I agree, too!

1:15:57.010 --> 1:15:59.080
Rather than end as a failed idol group,

1:16:00.750 --> 1:16:03.150
it's better to end as a No.1 disbanded group.

1:16:04.560 --> 1:16:06.460
I don't want to regret who I am, either.

1:16:10.530 --> 1:16:12.730
Wait, but

1:16:12.730 --> 1:16:14.930
No.1 in a music show is too much.

1:16:16.270 --> 1:16:17.550
Oh Hyun-ji.

1:16:18.700 --> 1:16:20.240
Remember what you said?

1:16:22.310 --> 1:16:23.740
You live only for today.

1:16:23.940 --> 1:16:25.340
You don't have a tomorrow.

1:16:25.680 --> 1:16:27.350
From now on,

1:16:27.750 --> 1:16:29.010
we don't have a tomorrow.

1:16:30.150 --> 1:16:31.380
We only live for today.

1:16:31.920 --> 1:16:33.600
So nothing is impossible.

1:16:35.420 --> 1:16:37.920
We've been scared for too long.

1:16:38.220 --> 1:16:39.760
We've been intimidated

1:16:40.460 --> 1:16:42.130
and diminished for too long.

1:16:44.660 --> 1:16:45.760
We have no tomorrow.

1:16:46.130 --> 1:16:47.530
So there's no need for that now.

1:16:50.870 --> 1:16:51.870
So.

1:16:53.640 --> 1:16:55.110
After we disband?

1:16:55.510 --> 1:16:56.810
What next?

1:17:02.550 --> 1:17:03.780
We go forward.

1:17:14.460 --> 1:17:15.530
Okay, then.

1:17:16.760 --> 1:17:18.800
First, we have to pass Reporter Mo.

1:17:21.070 --> 1:17:22.870
There's no way he'll write about us.

1:17:24.470 --> 1:17:25.770
I have an idea.

1:17:26.740 --> 1:17:28.340
It's evil, but...

1:17:32.140 --> 1:17:33.910
I like that.

1:17:34.580 --> 1:17:35.580
Great!

1:17:37.110 --> 1:17:38.480
Let's get No.1!

1:17:39.950 --> 1:17:40.850
On that stage,

1:17:40.850 --> 1:17:43.960
I'm going to say something to those

1:17:45.190 --> 1:17:46.620
who mocked Du-ho.

1:17:46.620 --> 1:17:47.620
What is it?

1:17:53.360 --> 1:17:54.400
Hey!

1:17:55.130 --> 1:17:57.100
You must be crazy. What are you doing?

1:17:57.100 --> 1:17:58.870
I'm really going to do it.

1:18:02.810 --> 1:18:05.110
You said you couldn't work this week.

1:18:05.110 --> 1:18:06.640
So we got someone else.

1:18:08.710 --> 1:18:10.450
We filled your time slots.

1:18:10.450 --> 1:18:11.950
She's in a difficult situation, too.

1:18:11.950 --> 1:18:13.630
I can't tell her to quit.

1:18:21.590 --> 1:18:23.260
I can't get a break.

1:18:29.000 --> 1:18:30.030
Thanks.

1:18:32.940 --> 1:18:37.310
If you have a place to stay, don't come home.

1:18:40.040 --> 1:18:41.750
Your dad is the same.

1:18:45.450 --> 1:18:47.490
Are you going to keep living like that, Mom?

1:18:47.820 --> 1:18:49.990
He's fine when he doesn't drink.

1:18:50.790 --> 1:18:52.220
At least, he doesn't hit me.

1:18:52.220 --> 1:18:54.190
Breaking stuff is the same!

1:18:55.030 --> 1:18:57.630
Aren't you scared when he's breaking things?

1:18:57.630 --> 1:18:59.840
Is it fun watching him?

1:19:01.140 --> 1:19:04.150
When will you be on TV?

1:19:05.200 --> 1:19:09.010
I wish I can see you often, even if it's just on TV.

1:19:20.450 --> 1:19:22.950
I have to be by your father's side.

1:19:23.820 --> 1:19:25.360
When you become famous,

1:19:25.360 --> 1:19:27.090
he won't keep silent.

1:19:27.560 --> 1:19:28.990
You know those people

1:19:29.460 --> 1:19:31.260
who parade their famous celebrity kids

1:19:31.260 --> 1:19:32.900
and screw people over and scam them.

1:19:33.900 --> 1:19:35.730
He'll do that and more.

1:19:36.100 --> 1:19:38.270
I have to be by his side to stop him.

1:19:58.960 --> 1:20:00.640
What's Kim Jenna doing?

1:20:01.060 --> 1:20:02.530
What do you think?

1:20:02.530 --> 1:20:04.060
She's probably devastated.

1:20:06.600 --> 1:20:07.600
Sir.

1:20:08.600 --> 1:20:10.670
Settle the compensation now

1:20:10.670 --> 1:20:12.300
and send them out with encouragement.

1:20:12.300 --> 1:20:15.240
Are you doing this to save puny money?

1:20:15.710 --> 1:20:18.410
Do you think that's why I'm doing that?

1:20:18.910 --> 1:20:22.450
With that mindset, I won't succeed anywhere.

1:20:23.680 --> 1:20:26.320
Then are you giving them a vaccination shot

1:20:26.320 --> 1:20:28.090
so they'll do well in the future?

1:20:28.090 --> 1:20:29.290
That's a good expression.

1:20:30.790 --> 1:20:31.690
Sir.

1:20:31.690 --> 1:20:33.130
Is your pride hurt

1:20:33.320 --> 1:20:35.790
because Jenna stood up against you?

1:20:43.570 --> 1:20:45.200
I'm American.

1:20:46.200 --> 1:20:47.800
What does that mean?

1:20:50.510 --> 1:20:51.610
Well...

1:20:52.040 --> 1:20:54.810
I'm asking if you're in a battle of pride with Jenna.

1:20:54.810 --> 1:20:57.580
She probably has no intention of doing that.

1:20:57.580 --> 1:20:59.320
What do you take me for? Seriously!

1:20:59.520 --> 1:21:01.420
I just caught that vibe.

1:21:07.360 --> 1:21:08.360
Come in.

1:21:10.160 --> 1:21:11.330
Director.

1:21:11.330 --> 1:21:13.600
You look terrible these days.

1:21:13.700 --> 1:21:14.660
Do I?

1:21:16.300 --> 1:21:18.270
Is anyone hiring a director?

1:21:18.270 --> 1:21:20.400
A peaceful and stressless place?

1:21:20.540 --> 1:21:22.010
Go look for one.

1:21:22.140 --> 1:21:23.870
I know you prefer not to see me.

1:21:30.610 --> 1:21:32.180
I guess you're not busy.

1:21:32.180 --> 1:21:33.850
Seeing a superstar like you coming here so often.

1:21:33.850 --> 1:21:36.450
I said I won't feature in Lune's song a long time ago.

1:21:37.290 --> 1:21:38.660
Why bring it up again?

1:21:38.990 --> 1:21:39.820
Why won't you?

1:21:39.820 --> 1:21:41.190
There's no reason not to.

1:21:42.330 --> 1:21:44.430
But there's a reason you have to.

1:21:44.430 --> 1:21:45.800
I don't like her.

1:21:46.200 --> 1:21:48.130
I don't sing for people I don't like.

1:21:48.130 --> 1:21:49.810
That's not professional.

1:21:50.630 --> 1:21:51.900
I don't care what you think.

1:21:51.900 --> 1:21:53.340
This is why

1:21:53.970 --> 1:21:56.610
I was going to get rid of your respirator long ago.

1:21:57.780 --> 1:21:59.340
You showed no promise of being a pro.

1:21:59.340 --> 1:22:01.180
I've come back alive. What will you do?

1:22:02.350 --> 1:22:04.580
But you've come into my hands. What will you do?

1:22:04.950 --> 1:22:06.250
Unbelievable.

1:22:10.950 --> 1:22:15.730
Oh! You know I'm not the old me, right?

1:22:22.570 --> 1:22:23.670
Where are you?

1:22:23.670 --> 1:22:24.670
I have something to say.

1:22:24.900 --> 1:22:25.900
Me, too.

1:22:30.170 --> 1:22:32.110
I know this will sound crazy.

1:22:33.040 --> 1:22:34.010
But I want to ask you a favor.

1:22:34.010 --> 1:22:35.350
I want to ask you a favor first.

1:22:36.580 --> 1:22:37.880
Let's start

1:22:40.780 --> 1:22:41.950
a rumor we're dating.

1:22:51.780 --> 1:22:55.080
Special thanks to Jung Woong-in and Kang Jae-jun
for their cameo appearance

1:23:13.850 --> 1:23:15.950
IDOL
IDOL: The Coup

1:23:15.950 --> 1:23:18.090
A battle of a man's pride is that juvenile.

1:23:18.090 --> 1:23:20.320
Why are you so reckless?

1:23:20.320 --> 1:23:23.190
I want to see if we really have no potential.

1:23:23.190 --> 1:23:24.030
Bye.

1:23:24.030 --> 1:23:25.300
If that's what you believe, then go.

1:23:25.300 --> 1:23:26.230
I'm a bit angry.

1:23:26.230 --> 1:23:27.700
I let you exploit me to this extent.

1:23:27.700 --> 1:23:29.030
Are you picking a fight with me?

1:23:29.030 --> 1:23:30.900
The type of person who will

1:23:30.900 --> 1:23:32.140
bite when cornered.

1:23:32.140 --> 1:23:33.770
What we really want?

1:23:32.140 --> 1:23:32.770
Exclusive Contract Cancellation Agreement

1:23:33.770 --> 1:23:34.570
You think it was money?

1:23:34.570 --> 1:23:36.340
This isn't such a simple matter!

1:23:36.340 --> 1:23:39.410
You can make it into a simple matter!

1:23:39.610 --> 1:23:40.410
Just wait and see.

1:23:40.410 --> 1:23:41.950
See how we pull this off.
